<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[117,768,924,1047]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis box="[154,404,924,948]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. – 
<collectingCountry box="[436,530,924,948]" name="Comoros" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Comoros</collectingCountry>
Archipelago; endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[144,387,957,981]" country="Comoros" name="Grande Comore" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Grande Comore island</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[402,465,957,981]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[103,128,1906,1926]" captionTargetBox="[103,1478,867,1886]" captionTargetId="figure-350@1.[128,1478,867,1881]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. – Comoros Archipelago (Union of the Comoros and Mayotte) showing distributions of Anisotes comorensis (Lindau) T. F. Daniel and A. mayottensis T. F. Daniel. The exact location of the sole collection of A. comorensis (Lindau) T. F. Daniel from Grande Comore is unknown." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5715286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5715286/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); the species is known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[218,265,990,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
collection made in 1886 from an undisclosed locale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[118,769,1064,1518]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis box="[156,277,1064,1088]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Discussion</emphasis>
. – There are 
<specimenCount box="[423,599,1064,1088]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" type="generic">three specimens</specimenCount>
at P, one annotated (recently) as the 
<typeStatus box="[346,436,1097,1121]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
and two as isotypes. No herbarium of deposit was cited in the protologue, and Humblot’s collections were widely distributed (LANJOUW &amp; STAFLEU, 1957) including to B, where Lindau worked on 
<taxonomicName box="[569,710,1196,1220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
<emphasis box="[569,710,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Acanthaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after 1892. If a single specimen at B was used by Lindau in creating his protologue, it would have been the 
<typeStatus box="[585,684,1262,1286]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
. Such a specimen is no longer extant at B. The specimen at P annotated as the 
<typeStatus box="[250,346,1328,1352]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
bears Lindau’s name in a handwriting that resembles that of Benoist rather than that of Lindau, and would thus appear to represent either a 
<typeStatus box="[540,623,1394,1418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">syntype</typeStatus>
or an isosyntype. This specimen (
<emphasis box="[342,492,1428,1452]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Humblot 1584</emphasis>
[P00184832]), which also bears the unpublished combination attributed to Benoist, is here designated as 
<typeStatus box="[328,430,1494,1518]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[467,761,1494,1518]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Himantochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comorensis">
<emphasis box="[467,761,1494,1518]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Himantochilus comorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[117,769,1534,1955]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
<bibRefCitation author="LINDAU, G." box="[156,314,1534,1558]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref5876" refString="LINDAU, G. (1894). Acanthaceae africanae. II. Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 20: 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1894">LINDAU (1894)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that 
<taxonomicName box="[471,625,1534,1558]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Himantochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comorensis">
<emphasis box="[471,625,1534,1558]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">H. comorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be distinguished from its congeners by the shape of the leaves and the much smaller flowers. 
<bibRefCitation author="BADEN, C." box="[412,582,1600,1624]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="623 - 664" refId="ref5546" refString="BADEN, C. (1981 b). The genus Anisotes (Acanthaceae), a taxonomic revision. Nordic J. Bot. 1: 623 - 664." type="journal article" year="1981">BADEN (1981b)</bibRefCitation>
treated Lindau’s 
<taxonomicName box="[118,270,1633,1657]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Himantochilus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comorensis">
<emphasis box="[118,270,1633,1657]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">H. comorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a “doubtful taxon”, did not see the 
<typeStatus box="[671,719,1633,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">type</typeStatus>
, and noted that based on Lindau’s description it was unlikely to pertain to 
<taxonomicName box="[192,283,1700,1724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,283,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Anisotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although 
<taxonomicName box="[407,498,1699,1723]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,498,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Anisotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not well distinguished morphologically from 
<taxonomicName box="[362,446,1733,1757]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[362,446,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Justicia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DANIEL, T. F. &amp; B. A &amp; MBOLA, F." box="[461,676,1733,1757]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="121 - 131" refId="ref5700" refString="DANIEL, T. F., B. A. V. MBOLA, F. ALMEDA &amp; P. B. PHILLIPSON (2007). Anisotes (Acanthaceae) in Madagascar. Proc. Calif. Acad. Sci. 58: 121 - 131." type="journal article" year="2007">DANIEL &amp; al., 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="DANIEL, T. F." pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="396 - 408" refId="ref5749" refString="DANIEL, T. F., R. LETSARA &amp; S. MARTIN- BRAVO (2013). Four new species of Anisotes (Acanthaceae) from Madagascar. Novon 22: 396 - 408." type="journal article" year="2013">DANIEL &amp; al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
), Lindau’s species contains the characteristic floral attributes of the former genus: relatively large (
<quantity box="[657,767,1799,1823]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.35" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="43.5" valueMax="65.0" valueMin="22.0">22-65 mm</quantity>
long) and strongly bilabiate corollas with ascending cochlear aestivation, a relatively short corolla tube (tube: corolla length up to 0.56, but usually 0.33 or less), a hoodlike and internally rugulate upper lip, and a lower lip that is usually recoiled.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[843,1494,281,402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">
Pollen of this species (
<figureCitation box="[1130,1197,281,305]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[118,143,1873,1893]" captionTargetBox="[120,1493,734,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-268@4.[386,1227,777,1810]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. – Pollen of Anisotes Nees in the Comoros Archipelago. A-B. Anisotes mayottensis T. F. Daniel; C-D. A. comorensis (Lindau) T. F. Daniel; A. Apertural view; B. Interapertural view; C. pertural view; D. Interapertural view. [A-B: Pascal 936, CS; C-D: Humblot 1584, P]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5715288" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5715288/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) is two-colporate with two pseudocolpi in each mesocolpium. Similar pollen was noted in 
<taxonomicName authority="T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martin-Bravo" authorityName="T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martin-Bravo" box="[870,1493,345,369]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Anisotes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subcoriaceus">
<emphasis box="[870,1101,345,369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Anisotes subcoriaceus</emphasis>
T. F. Daniel, Letsara &amp; Martín-Bravo
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[902,1031,378,402]" name="Madagascar" pageId="6" pageNumber="51">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DANIEL, T. F." box="[1045,1256,378,402]" pageId="6" pageNumber="51" pagination="396 - 408" refId="ref5749" refString="DANIEL, T. F., R. LETSARA &amp; S. MARTIN- BRAVO (2013). Four new species of Anisotes (Acanthaceae) from Madagascar. Novon 22: 396 - 408." type="journal article" year="2013">DANIEL &amp; al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
